      "step_idx": 4,
      "role": "RecyclingRate_Expert",
      "content": "We don't seem to have the URL, but generally speaking, the recycling rate for bottles in the U.S. is around $0.10 per bottle in states with a bottle deposit scheme. \n\nLet\u2019s proceed with this general information to calculate the amount earned.\n\nFirst, let's verify the calculation of the number of water bottles consumed and the total distance:\n1. Distance traveled: 3200 miles.\n2. Number of water bottles consumed: 160 bottles (as 5 bottles per 100 miles).\n\nNow, recalculating:\n\\[\n\\text{Total Amount of Money Received} = \\text{Number of Water Bottles} \\times \\text{Recycling Rate per Bottle}\n\\]\nGiven: \n\\[\n\\text{Recycling Rate per Bottle} = \\$0.10\n\\]\n\\[\n\\text{Total Amount of Money Received} = 160 \\times 0.10 = \\$16.00\n\\]\n\nCan you please provide the Wikipedia link to confirm this recycling rate?"
